      <section id="id24577302">
        <title>THE LARGE YELLOW BALL</title>
        <para id="id25053086"/>
        <para id="id17147882">The sun is actually a very big star that looks like a ball of fire in the middle of the universe. It provides the light and warmth that all living things need for growth. The energy that is released within the sun causes the sun to shine. Sunspots on the surface of the sun are seen frequently.</para>
        <figure id="id24820678">
          <media id="id24820678_media" alt="">
            <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics1-6255.png" id="id24820678__onlineimage" height="241" width="633"/>
          </media>
        </figure>
        <para id="id24874012">Hold a group discussion about the following:</para>
        <list id="id8318897" list-type="bulleted">
          <item>Where does the sun rise in the morning?</item>
          <item>Where does the sun set in the evening?</item>
          <item>Where do you think the sun goes at night?</item>
        </list>
        <para id="id25012057">Keep a record of the sunrise and sunset times for a period of two weeks. What have you discovered? </para>
      </section>
